00:00:44.440 --> 00:00:46.660
First, we're actually
going to define engagement,

00:00:46.660 --> 00:00:49.881
because it's a pretty
straightforward topic,

00:00:49.881 --> 00:00:51.380
but there's a couple
of distinctions

00:00:51.380 --> 00:00:53.090
that I want to make
just to kind of level

00:00:53.090 --> 00:00:55.674
set-- make sure that we're all
talking about the same thing.

00:00:55.674 --> 00:00:57.840
And then we're going to
talk about probably the core

00:00:57.840 --> 00:01:01.410
component here, actually
designing games for engagement.

00:01:01.410 --> 00:01:03.880
We're going to talk about
Google Play game services,

00:01:03.880 --> 00:01:07.289
which the way that Ben and
John described it just now,

00:01:07.289 --> 00:01:08.080
it's quite obvious.

00:01:08.080 --> 00:01:11.670
It is a tool box for creating a
great engagement for your game.

00:01:11.670 --> 00:01:14.430
It is literally all the
tools that you'll ever need.

00:01:14.430 --> 00:01:15.210
And then number
four, we're going

00:01:15.210 --> 00:01:17.543
to talk about community,
because community is very, very

00:01:17.543 --> 00:01:22.370
important-- the way that you,
as developers, engage users

00:01:22.370 --> 00:01:24.900
with your game.

00:01:24.900 --> 00:01:27.340
So what is engagement?

00:01:27.340 --> 00:01:29.250
I think everybody here
probably knows how

00:01:29.250 --> 00:01:31.390
to measure engagement for sure.

00:01:31.390 --> 00:01:35.020
I mean, we talk about
retention rates, D1, D7, D30.

00:01:35.020 --> 00:01:36.610
And certainly one
way we figure out

00:01:36.610 --> 00:01:38.490
how people are engaging
with their game,

00:01:38.490 --> 00:01:40.250
if they're sticking
around and playing.

00:01:40.250 --> 00:01:43.309
We talk about sessions per
day, session length as well.

00:01:43.309 --> 00:01:45.100
And there's another
one that we talk about,

00:01:45.100 --> 00:01:47.570
which is like a stickiness
factor, which is Daily Active

00:01:47.570 --> 00:01:50.380
Users over Monthly Active
Users-- DAU over MAU--

00:01:50.380 --> 00:01:52.070
it's a percentage.

00:01:52.070 --> 00:01:54.140
But what is
engagement in essence?

00:01:54.140 --> 00:01:56.204
We know how to measure
it, but what is it?

00:01:56.204 --> 00:01:57.620
There's actually
kind of two types

00:01:57.620 --> 00:02:00.150
that I want to talk about.

00:02:00.150 --> 00:02:02.430
First type is direct engagement.

00:02:02.430 --> 00:02:05.220
And this is the one that we see
on a pretty much daily basis.

00:02:05.220 --> 00:02:06.760
And it's kind of
the obvious one.

00:02:06.760 --> 00:02:08.720
It's when people are
actually using your game

00:02:08.720 --> 00:02:10.100
and playing your game.

00:02:10.100 --> 00:02:12.010
This is a game called Two Dots.

00:02:12.010 --> 00:02:14.227
This is right after
I finished level 123.

00:02:14.227 --> 00:02:15.310
This is direct engagement.

00:02:15.310 --> 00:02:15.955
It's very straightforward.

00:02:15.955 --> 00:02:17.720
It's everything players
do while directly

00:02:17.720 --> 00:02:19.155
interacting with the game.

00:02:19.155 --> 00:02:21.530
But there's a second type--
and we'll get to that later--

00:02:21.530 --> 00:02:23.071
but I just wanted
to call it out now,

00:02:23.071 --> 00:02:25.690
because it's also
very, very critical.

00:02:25.690 --> 00:02:28.980
I call it community engagement.

00:02:28.980 --> 00:02:30.850
Now think about it this way.

00:02:30.850 --> 00:02:32.289
Think about your hobbies.

00:02:32.289 --> 00:02:33.580
And this is really interesting.

00:02:33.580 --> 00:02:37.280
I came up with this example
before I saw the opening video

00:02:37.280 --> 00:02:40.770
that came out before Purnima
kind of gave the opening

00:02:40.770 --> 00:02:41.930
keynote this morning.

00:02:41.930 --> 00:02:43.750
I thought about this
example about fishing.

00:02:43.750 --> 00:02:45.750
And there's apparently
an incredible fishing app

00:02:45.750 --> 00:02:48.370
out there, which is exactly
the type of thing that

00:02:48.370 --> 00:02:51.600
drives community engagement
with a hobby of fishing.

00:02:51.600 --> 00:02:53.570
So it's actually
really well timed.

00:02:53.570 --> 00:02:56.410
And it's one of those
moments of synchronicity

00:02:56.410 --> 00:02:58.320
I couldn't have
planned any better.

00:02:58.320 --> 00:03:02.380
So for example, when I
was a little bit younger,

00:03:02.380 --> 00:03:04.780
I was visiting my hometown
of Houston, Texas, which

00:03:04.780 --> 00:03:07.240
is right on the Gulf of
Mexico and the United States.

00:03:07.240 --> 00:03:09.850
It's a great little fishing
town right outside of it

00:03:09.850 --> 00:03:10.630
called Galveston.

00:03:10.630 --> 00:03:13.090
And my friends and I decided
one night let's just go out

00:03:13.090 --> 00:03:14.850
fishing, because it was
just a nice beautiful night

00:03:14.850 --> 00:03:16.220
and we went out, and we did it.

00:03:16.220 --> 00:03:19.329
We caught a 10-kilo
fish last 10 minutes

00:03:19.329 --> 00:03:20.370
we were out on the ocean.

00:03:20.370 --> 00:03:22.510
And honestly, it was
one of the best nights

00:03:22.510 --> 00:03:25.300
I've ever had as a fisherman.

00:03:25.300 --> 00:03:27.100
That right there, me
telling you this story

00:03:27.100 --> 00:03:29.140
and talking about it, you
engaging with that app

00:03:29.140 --> 00:03:33.040
that we showed earlier
today in the video, that's

00:03:33.040 --> 00:03:34.390
community engagement.

00:03:34.390 --> 00:03:36.210
It's everything that
you do when you're

00:03:36.210 --> 00:03:39.830
engaging in a hobby or a
game when you're not actually

00:03:39.830 --> 00:03:42.280
engaging in the
hobby or the game.

00:03:42.280 --> 00:03:44.340
When I'm out casting
my reel or when

00:03:44.340 --> 00:03:46.520
I'm out playing Two
Dots or some other game,

00:03:46.520 --> 00:03:47.954
that's direct engagement.

00:03:47.954 --> 00:03:49.620
The second type is
community engagement,

00:03:49.620 --> 00:03:51.499
but it's equally important.

00:03:51.499 --> 00:03:52.790
We'll get to exactly why later.

00:03:55.710 --> 00:03:58.390
Designing games for engagement.

00:03:58.390 --> 00:04:01.630
So we've defined exactly
what engagement is.

00:04:01.630 --> 00:04:04.950
Now let's talk about
how to design for it.

00:04:04.950 --> 00:04:07.514
And I could go through
game after game after game

00:04:07.514 --> 00:04:09.680
after game, and tell you
exactly how these games are

00:04:09.680 --> 00:04:12.551
designed for engagement, but
that wouldn't be super helpful.

00:04:12.551 --> 00:04:14.050
So I've decided to
kind of narrow it

00:04:14.050 --> 00:04:16.496
down to three
games-- three games

00:04:16.496 --> 00:04:18.829
that I've been playing for a
very, very long time, three

00:04:18.829 --> 00:04:20.750
games that are all
very, very different,

00:04:20.750 --> 00:04:22.400
three games that have
been out actually

00:04:22.400 --> 00:04:25.090
all for about the same amount of
time-- about a year and a half

00:04:25.090 --> 00:04:27.560
and are all very, very
