00:16:14.230 --> 00:16:15.235
Why is this important?

00:16:20.815 --> 00:16:22.690
You might have seen one
of these in the past.

00:16:22.690 --> 00:16:26.510
This is a pretty typical
marketing 101 marketing curve.

00:16:26.510 --> 00:16:30.285
This is tracking the adoption
of a product over time.

00:16:30.285 --> 00:16:32.285
You've got your innovators,
your early adopters,

00:16:32.285 --> 00:16:36.430
your early majority, late
majority and your laggards.

00:16:36.430 --> 00:16:38.330
If you've read a
Malcolm Gladwell's book,

00:16:38.330 --> 00:16:40.620
you've definitely
seen this as well.

00:16:40.620 --> 00:16:43.750
Now here's the thing.

00:16:43.750 --> 00:16:48.640
The people that influence
other people to download games,

00:16:48.640 --> 00:16:53.850
to go fishing, to buy a
magazine, to try a restaurant,

00:16:53.850 --> 00:16:55.970
those people are
actually involved

00:16:55.970 --> 00:16:57.680
in community engagement.

00:16:57.680 --> 00:16:58.900
And they're the influencers.

00:16:58.900 --> 00:17:00.400
They are the
influencers, the mavens

00:17:00.400 --> 00:17:01.629
that you always hear about.

00:17:01.629 --> 00:17:03.420
And they actually kind
of reside over here.

00:17:03.420 --> 00:17:06.135
They're the most engaged
people in whatever product

00:17:06.135 --> 00:17:07.010
you're talking about.

00:17:07.010 --> 00:17:10.319
This applies to just
about any industry.

00:17:10.319 --> 00:17:11.940
That's why this is important.

00:17:11.940 --> 00:17:14.859
When you get people
talking about your game,

00:17:14.859 --> 00:17:17.280
when you get people posting
on various social medias

00:17:17.280 --> 00:17:20.670
about your game, when
you get people creating

00:17:20.670 --> 00:17:23.300
YouTube videos-- anything
that pretty much,

00:17:23.300 --> 00:17:27.260
again, falls into that category
of community engagement--

00:17:27.260 --> 00:17:31.700
that's so critical, because
community is actually

00:17:31.700 --> 00:17:34.110
an engagement and marketing
channel for your game.

00:17:34.110 --> 00:17:35.880
And this is the critical thing.

00:17:35.880 --> 00:17:39.200
User acquisition is incredibly
expensive these days.

00:17:39.200 --> 00:17:41.390
Sometimes it costs
upwards of $15

00:17:41.390 --> 00:17:46.660
to get a user onto a platform
or on pretty much any platform.

00:17:46.660 --> 00:17:49.150
However community
engagement-- the fact

00:17:49.150 --> 00:17:54.030
that it can drive new users
to your game for free--

00:17:54.030 --> 00:17:54.840
it's incredible.

00:17:54.840 --> 00:17:56.340
It's one of the
most powerful things

00:17:56.340 --> 00:17:59.820
that you can do to drive
long-term engagement, long-term

00:17:59.820 --> 00:18:01.135
acquisition with your game.

00:18:04.950 --> 00:18:08.010
One last point I'd like to
